<paragraph id="F05D0B52E22F3147FF77FC50FDAD645A" blockId="3.[151,1438,843,1218]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1438,152,371]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="425" pageId="3" pageNumber="424">
<emphasis id="C296D740E22F3140FF77FC50FECC669B" bold="true" box="[198,275,920,946]" pageId="3" pageNumber="424">Notes.</emphasis>
Three specimens of this taxon, recently described by 
<bibRefCitation id="947376A3E22F3140FC3CFC51FBEC669A" author="Stuben, P. E." box="[909,1075,921,947]" pageId="3" pageNumber="424" pagination="26 - 126" refId="ref4221" refString="Stuben, P. E. (2007) Vorstudien zu einer Revision der westpalarktischen &quot; Torneumatini &quot; - Taxonomie, Biologie und Okologie (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Cryptorhynchinae) - Ein Blick unter die &quot; Grasnarbe des Lebens &quot; - Mit 943 Abbildungen, 45 Tafeln, 6 REM-Aufnahmen, 63 Verbreitungskarten. Snudebiller, 8, 26 - 126." type="book chapter" year="2007">Stüben (2007)</bibRefCitation>
as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="37E270D1E22F3140FAA4FC51FE9066F3" authority="F. Solari, 1937" authorityName="F. Solari" authorityYear="1937" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Torneuma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curtulum">
<emphasis id="C296D740E22F3140FAA4FC51FA43669B" box="[1301,1436,921,946]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="424">T. curtulum</emphasis>
F. 
<bibRefCitation id="947376A3E22F3140FF07FC08FE9066F3" author="Solari, F." box="[182,335,960,986]" pageId="3" pageNumber="424" pagination="14 - 19" refId="ref4144" refString="Solari, F. (1937) Prodromo utile per la revisione dei Torneumatini. Bollettino della Societa entomologica Italiana, 68 (1 - 2), 14 - 19." type="journal article" year="1937">Solari, 1937</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from two rather close localities of eastern 
<collectingRegion id="3226C5B0E22F3140FCDBFC08FC0E66F3" box="[874,977,960,986]" country="Italy" name="Sardegna" pageId="3" pageNumber="424">Sardinia</collectingRegion>
(Escalapiano, and Mt. Narba east of Muravera) were found at Case Marganai, near Iglesias. The known distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="37E270D1E22F3140FB3CFC2FFEF7610E" authority="F. Solari, 1937" authorityName="F. Solari" authorityYear="1937" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Torneuma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curtulum">
<emphasis id="C296D740E22F3140FB3CFC2FFAA26129" box="[1165,1405,999,1024]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="424">Torneuma curtulum</emphasis>
F. 
<bibRefCitation id="947376A3E22F3140FF26FBC5FEF7610E" author="Solari, F." box="[151,296,1037,1063]" pageId="3" pageNumber="424" pagination="14 - 19" refId="ref4144" refString="Solari, F. (1937) Prodromo utile per la revisione dei Torneumatini. Bollettino della Societa entomologica Italiana, 68 (1 - 2), 14 - 19." type="journal article" year="1937">Solari, 1937</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is, according to our personal records (
<figureCitation id="68D917D7E22F3140FD40FBC5FCEA610E" box="[753,821,1037,1063]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,255,1970,1994]" captionTargetBox="[446,1139,1265,1944]" captionTargetId="figure-339@3.[409,1177,1245,1944]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Distribution in Sardinia of Torneuma curtulum (left) and T. vastum (right). Triangles indicate type localities." pageId="3" pageNumber="424">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
), much more widespread than that given by 
<bibRefCitation id="947376A3E22F3140FAFBFBC5FF376167" author="Stuben, P. E." pageId="3" pageNumber="424" pagination="26 - 126" refId="ref4221" refString="Stuben, P. E. (2007) Vorstudien zu einer Revision der westpalarktischen &quot; Torneumatini &quot; - Taxonomie, Biologie und Okologie (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Cryptorhynchinae) - Ein Blick unter die &quot; Grasnarbe des Lebens &quot; - Mit 943 Abbildungen, 45 Tafeln, 6 REM-Aufnahmen, 63 Verbreitungskarten. Snudebiller, 8, 26 - 126." type="book chapter" year="2007">Stüben (2007)</bibRefCitation>
, who only knew this weevil from Domusnovas, Flumentorgius and Fluminimaggiore, all localities in western 
<collectingRegion id="3226C5B0E22F3140FF4BFB92FE83615D" box="[250,348,1114,1140]" country="Italy" name="Sardegna" pageId="3" pageNumber="424">Sardinia</collectingRegion>
close to the present one. A specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="37E270D1E22F3140FC8EFB93FC18615D" authorityName="F. Solari" authorityYear="1937" box="[831,967,1115,1140]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Torneuma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curtulum">
<emphasis id="C296D740E22F3140FC8EFB93FC18615D" box="[831,967,1115,1140]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="424">T. curtulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected at Mamenga, just a short distance from Case Marganai (where the above-mentioned 
<specimenCount id="E6E4C0DBE22F3140FCE9FB49FC3561B2" box="[856,1002,1153,1179]" pageId="3" pageNumber="424" type="generic">3 specimens</specimenCount>
were found), so the two taxa can be considered as sympatric. This implies that 
<taxonomicName id="37E270D1E22F3140FD16FB60FBF561EB" authority="Stuben, 2007" authorityName="Stuben" authorityYear="2007" box="[679,1066,1192,1218]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Torneuma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vastum">
<emphasis id="C296D740E22F3140FD16FB60FC5E61E8" box="[679,897,1192,1217]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="424">Torneuma vastum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="947376A3E22F3140FC3BFB60FBF561EB" author="Stuben, P. E." box="[906,1066,1192,1218]" pageId="3" pageNumber="424" pagination="26 - 126" refId="ref4221" refString="Stuben, P. E. (2007) Vorstudien zu einer Revision der westpalarktischen &quot; Torneumatini &quot; - Taxonomie, Biologie und Okologie (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Cryptorhynchinae) - Ein Blick unter die &quot; Grasnarbe des Lebens &quot; - Mit 943 Abbildungen, 45 Tafeln, 6 REM-Aufnahmen, 63 Verbreitungskarten. Snudebiller, 8, 26 - 126." type="book chapter" year="2007">Stüben, 2007</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="C296D740E22F3140FB8FFB6FFB7161E8" bold="true" box="[1086,1198,1191,1217]" pageId="3" pageNumber="424">stat. rev.</emphasis>
) is a self-standing species, and not a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="37E270D1E2283147FDA5FF50FD446598" authorityName="F. Solari" authorityYear="1937" box="[532,667,152,178]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Torneuma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="425" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curtulum">
<emphasis id="C296D740E2283147FDA5FF50FDFD6598" box="[532,546,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="425">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="C296D740E2283147FD80FF50FD446598" box="[561,667,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="425">curtulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. For the subtle characters which differentiate 
<taxonomicName id="37E270D1E2283147FB06FF50FAE16598" authorityName="F. Solari" authorityYear="1937" box="[1207,1342,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Torneuma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="425" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curtulum">
<emphasis id="C296D740E2283147FB06FF50FAE16598" box="[1207,1342,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="425">T. curtulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="37E270D1E2283147FA37FF50FF3565F1" authorityName="Stuben" authorityYear="2007" baseAuthorityName="Stuben" baseAuthorityYear="2007" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Torneuma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="425" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vastum">
<emphasis id="C296D740E2283147FA37FF50FF3565F1" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="425">T. vastum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
see 
<bibRefCitation id="947376A3E2283147FE91FF76FE1565F1" author="Stuben, P. E." box="[288,458,190,216]" pageId="4" pageNumber="425" pagination="26 - 126" refId="ref4221" refString="Stuben, P. E. (2007) Vorstudien zu einer Revision der westpalarktischen &quot; Torneumatini &quot; - Taxonomie, Biologie und Okologie (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Cryptorhynchinae) - Ein Blick unter die &quot; Grasnarbe des Lebens &quot; - Mit 943 Abbildungen, 45 Tafeln, 6 REM-Aufnahmen, 63 Verbreitungskarten. Snudebiller, 8, 26 - 126." type="book chapter" year="2007">Stüben (2007)</bibRefCitation>
, and for their distribution see 
<figureCitation id="68D917D7E2283147FC9FFF76FCAB65F1" box="[814,884,190,216]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,255,1970,1994]" captionTargetBox="[446,1139,1265,1944]" captionTargetId="figure-339@3.[409,1177,1245,1944]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Distribution in Sardinia of Torneuma curtulum (left) and T. vastum (right). Triangles indicate type localities." pageId="4" pageNumber="425">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
. Among the inaccuracies of the cited paper by 
<bibRefCitation id="947376A3E2283147FF26FF2DFEE265D6" author="Stuben, P. E." box="[151,317,229,255]" pageId="4" pageNumber="425" pagination="26 - 126" refId="ref4221" refString="Stuben, P. E. (2007) Vorstudien zu einer Revision der westpalarktischen &quot; Torneumatini &quot; - Taxonomie, Biologie und Okologie (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Cryptorhynchinae) - Ein Blick unter die &quot; Grasnarbe des Lebens &quot; - Mit 943 Abbildungen, 45 Tafeln, 6 REM-Aufnahmen, 63 Verbreitungskarten. Snudebiller, 8, 26 - 126." type="book chapter" year="2007">Stüben (2007)</bibRefCitation>
are the descriptions of subspecies of the same species the distributional areas of which largely overlap, a circumstance that clearly weakens the even explicit provisional taxonomy proposed by this author. In the future we will publish additional changes affecting the taxonomy of the 
<taxonomicName id="37E270D1E2283147FBDCFEFAFACA6465" authorityName="Bedel" authorityYear="1884" box="[1133,1301,306,332]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="425" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Torneumatini">Torneumatini</taxonomicName>
, which are beyond the purpose of the present paper.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
